	(text "KevJu:\nThis capacitor is 47pF on the IBM \nschematic. I don't understand the \npoint of a 47pF cap in parallel \nwith the several-thousand pF cap \nformed by the GND and 5V planes.\nAccording to Murata simsurfer data, \na 100nF or 47nF leaded cap has lower\nimpedance than a 47pF part at\nevery frequency, usually by 1 or 2\norders of magnitude.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
